title: M cycles
extract: Periodic, repetitive sequence of events in a process that plays out over time (such as a life cycle), or keeps on going indefinitely (such as a cash cycle). ... Cycles within a year are called seasonal patterns or variations. 3. Single execution of a complete set of operations in a process, from beginning to end.
